name: integer_i16_negative_one
description: |
  This is -1, represented with every bit set in two's-complement i16. It is the
  divisor that makes i16 minimum division overflow, and it commonly exposes
  differences between arithmetic and logical right shifts, sign extension,
  and signed-to-unsigned conversion. The same bytes represent u16 maximum.
format: hex
decode-as: i16
pair:
  - with: ../u16/maximum.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i16"
  - "negative"
  - "division"
  - "sign-extension"
  - "conversion"
  - "two's-complement"
  - "all-bits-set"
---
ff ff # -1
